Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.31,0:00:05.35,Location,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(204,200)\pos(360,365)}Jahreszeit Hotel\N(Frankfurt)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.80,0:00:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Red Rose Mansion experiment is still going...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.89,0:00:26.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The devil got himself a disciple.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.81,0:00:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man with glasses...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.10,0:00:33.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The survivor from the Red Rose Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.78,0:00:36.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter... {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.66,0:00:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.71,0:00:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is trying to control the devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.90,0:01:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please follow that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.66,0:01:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He ran!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.17,0:03:22.38,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(221,100)\pos(360,344)}A Fun Dining Table
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.38,0:03:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.84,0:03:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.39,0:03:50.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.43,0:03:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.85,0:03:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.98,0:03:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're very lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.73,0:03:58.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You only sprained your leg.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.73,0:04:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From what I can tell, you didn't hit\Nyour head all that hard, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though I'm not an expert like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.03,0:04:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.53,0:04:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.03,0:04:10.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A genius brain surgeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.70,0:04:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I read about you in the newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.37,0:04:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.79,0:04:16.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a local dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.12,0:04:17.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The name's Milan Kolasch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.29,0:04:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I happened to see you get hit by a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.80,0:04:24.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The car that hit you sped off in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.38,0:04:26.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should stay in bed for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.26,0:04:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'll cause you trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.35,0:04:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wobbling around here with that leg of yours...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.85,0:04:37.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and catching the attention of the\Npolice would trouble me more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.02,0:04:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.07,0:04:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Turkish district in Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.57,0:04:45.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turkish district?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.49,0:04:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should say it used to be the Turkish district.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:53.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're tearing down all the buildings around\Nhere for redevelopment or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.95,0:04:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most of the Turks who were living here...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.75,0:04:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,moved to another location.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.04,0:05:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when they were attacked by the extreme right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.92,0:05:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they fought back together.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.05,0:05:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is Caf{\fnMeiryo U}é{\fnNarkisim} Bahir gone, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.01,0:05:10.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.05,0:05:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's long gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.76,0:05:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know this area?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.31,0:05:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.98,0:05:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you can get up...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.94,0:05:21.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you want to have your meal over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.11,0:05:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It tastes better when you eat with everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.65,0:05:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're having Vietnamese food today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.53,0:05:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minh made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.32,0:05:32.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pho Ga and Cha Gio Tom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.12,0:05:37.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minh's Vietnamese dishes are exceptional.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.91,0:05:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hold back, eat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.25,0:05:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.21,0:05:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love pork, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.01,0:05:52.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turkish people don't eat pork.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.39,0:05:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not too fond of Czech food.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.56,0:05:58.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's because Milan can't cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.68,0:06:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.06,0:06:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone takes turns making food\Nfrom their home country.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.65,0:06:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's luxurious to be able to taste food from different\Ncountries every day, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.24,0:06:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma, you're Japanese right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.40,0:06:12.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does Japanese food taste like?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.70,0:06:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Japanese food, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.58,0:06:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, make us some.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.12,0:06:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I can't wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.75,0:06:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.16,0:06:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Katsudon requires pork.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.29,0:06:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sushi...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.54,0:06:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are probably people who can't eat raw fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.38,0:06:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about Oyakodon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.38,0:06:35.32,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyakodon -Chicken and egg on rice, also known as parent and child donburi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.44,0:06:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oyakodon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.67,0:06:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.59,0:06:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You put chicken on top of rice,\Ncovered in soy sauce and eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.35,0:06:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is that Oyakodon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.47,0:06:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The chicken is the parent, and the eggs are the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.10,0:06:41.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why it's called Oyakodon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.23,0:06:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Japanese food names sure are amusing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.32,0:06:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chicken and egg together means parent and child!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.82,0:06:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.62,0:06:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.24,0:07:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't like the food?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.96,0:07:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.88,0:07:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just been so long...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.38,0:07:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,since I had such delicious food...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.67,0:07:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I had such an enjoyable meal...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.48,0:07:26.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.23,0:07:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.36,0:07:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how long it'll take...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.49,0:07:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before I can walk again?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.45,0:07:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any time to waste...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.34,0:07:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.14,0:07:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.47,0:08:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.06,0:08:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A report on the actions taken by Peter {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.19,0:08:08.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you think it was strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.86,0:08:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason the police were so well-organized...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.90,0:08:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't because they were trying to catch you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.28,0:08:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were originally on the lookout for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.95,0:08:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to kill Peter {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.05,0:08:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.55,0:08:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.38,0:08:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be able to make good\Nones that could fly really far.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.89,0:08:43.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milan is good at making paper airplanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.52,0:08:47.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They would fly all the way to the roofs over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.02,0:08:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.52,0:08:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milan always said to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.52,0:08:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He always promised us...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:57.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someday, we'll go much farther than those roofs.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.65,0:09:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We'll go to Turkey, Vietnam, and \N even the Czech Republic.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.33,0:09:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's go see everyone's homelands.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.87,0:09:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.66,0:09:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.79,0:09:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.63,0:09:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no good after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.05,0:09:16.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why won't it fly?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.47,0:09:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.51,0:09:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to kill Peter {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.97,0:09:25.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.27,0:09:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you do such a thing, Mr. Milan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.44,0:09:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.31,0:09:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man named Peter {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.23,0:09:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is a devil.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.73,0:09:38.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In 1989...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.28,0:09:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the night before the fall of the Communist\NParty in Czechoslovakia...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.91,0:09:44.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he escaped into this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.24,0:09:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek lived here in Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.12,0:09:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He became a teacher, and he started teaching German.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.83,0:09:54.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a quiet man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.17,0:09:57.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, somewhere down the road...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.01,0:09:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the children started to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.68,0:10:03.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Children who attended his class committed\Nsuicide, one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.56,0:10:06.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.72,0:10:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they started to show extreme aggression.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.14,0:10:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And finally, one day...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.35,0:10:16.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a riot broke out, and the children tried to kill each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.82,0:10:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to an institute where the ringleader\Nof that incident was being held.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.28,0:10:25.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He quietly said to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.66,0:10:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that he wanted to hurry back to the book readings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.37,0:10:30.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Book readings?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.91,0:10:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The child committed suicide in the institute that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.92,0:10:40.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.22,0:10:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek left town during the disturbance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.85,0:10:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next time he appeared in this town...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.72,0:10:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was like a different person.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.48,0:10:53.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He took control of the underground\Norganization in Frankfurt...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.73,0:10:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and had ties with the extreme right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.57,0:10:57.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.44,0:11:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he used them to start purging this neighborhood\Nof Turks and other foreigners.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.32,0:11:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what he's trying to accomplish in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.08,0:11:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, the pinnacle of his violence...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.87,0:11:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was the burning of the Turkish district in 1996.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.96,0:11:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know about that incident, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.92,0:11:21.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.34,0:11:22.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it on the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.55,0:11:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The townspeople formed a vigilance\N\Ncommittee to try to oppose them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.68,0:11:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.47,0:11:33.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The five leaders of the vigilance committee...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.64,0:11:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all died strange deaths...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.27,0:11:38.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in just three months.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.32,0:11:41.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The five people who died were...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.82,0:11:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Suleiman's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.40,0:11:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tung's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.91,0:11:46.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Minh's husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.78,0:11:48.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mustafa's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.33,0:11:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Shemel's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.16,0:11:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.75,0:11:56.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.79,0:11:58.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by Peter {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.26,0:12:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know why you were watching {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.59,0:12:06.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But let me just say this...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.39,0:12:09.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who will kill {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.81,0:12:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.41,0:12:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.78,0:12:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think this one is pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.83,0:12:23.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.91,0:12:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I have to try.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.93,0:12:29.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some things are impossible, no matter how hard you try.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.04,0:12:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.00,0:12:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We know we can't go on vacation to Turkey or Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.84,0:12:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care if I go on a trip or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.80,0:12:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy as long as I can live\Nwith Milan and Tung like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.76,0:12:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.23,0:12:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, it's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:48.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This one will fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.86,0:12:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.98,0:12:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.49,0:12:57.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yay! It's flying!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.99,0:12:59.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.20,0:13:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt it'll fly over to the roof on\Nthe other side like Mr. Milan's.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.04,0:13:06.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's still flying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.25,0:13:08.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you glad we didn't give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.08,0:13:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.34,0:13:14.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't give up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.40,0:13:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's my gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.16,0:13:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you put the gun that was in my drawer?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.29,0:13:48.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My chance to shoot {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek has come.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.79,0:13:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.33,0:13:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.87,0:13:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let you do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.84,0:14:01.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't give you back your gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.68,0:14:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the gun I found in your coat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.97,0:14:09.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to use the gun I trained with and am\Nfamiliar with when I do the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.02,0:14:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.60,0:14:15.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a family now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.40,0:14:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.86,0:14:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been following {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek's actions for a long time now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.36,0:14:24.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never had as good a chance to do {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek in.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.83,0:14:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.79,0:14:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do this, Mr. Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.04,0:14:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.71,0:14:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't try to get in my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.62,0:14:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you get revenge now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.29,0:14:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can't bring back the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.55,0:14:40.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, you should think about the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.21,0:14:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have the right to tell me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.80,0:14:45.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Milan...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.60,0:14:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I are the same, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.48,0:14:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've done some checking up on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.19,0:14:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If what you claim is true...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.27,0:15:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you and I are both trying to do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.61,0:15:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wasn't always like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.53,0:15:08.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The person I knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.53,0:15:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,wasn't a devil like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.08,0:15:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Peter {\fnMeiryo U}Č{\fnNarkisim}apek and I are childhood\Nfriends from the same country.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.25,0:15:20.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought him into this country!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.38,0:15:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what's on the other side of the border?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.72,0:15:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not allowed to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.51,0:15:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're not allowed to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.35,0:15:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.64,0:15:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the other side of the border is a wonderful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.89,0:15:37.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a town that's always bright at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.36,0:15:39.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, Peter?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.07,0:15:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who did you hear that from?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.94,0:15:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Gregor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.40,0:15:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's an alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.32,0:15:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I heard that on the other side of the border...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.36,0:15:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there are things that make people\Nworthless, like Mr. Gregor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.70,0:15:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Things that make people worthless, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.41,0:15:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.50,0:15:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you want to see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.08,0:15:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.55,0:16:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's riding the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.75,0:16:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're good, Milan!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.92,0:16:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's flying! It's flying
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.47,0:16:05.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.47,0:16:07.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could go over the border if it keeps flying like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.93,0:16:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go see what it's like on the other side for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.39,0:16:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We grew up in a town near the border\Nof Czechoslovakia and Austria.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.06,0:16:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the son of a craftsman.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.48,0:16:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was the son of a government official.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.19,0:16:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.11,0:16:23.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,strangely, he and I got along well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.40,0:16:27.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In 1989...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.36,0:16:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when the Czechoslovakian Communist Party collapsed...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.28,0:16:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who helped him escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.87,0:16:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who brought that devil to this country...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.08,0:16:41.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.07,0:16:48.68,Name,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(320,457)\fad(461)}Prague
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.64,0:16:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was really worried about you during\Nthe Soviet invasion last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:16:59.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of my friends were dragged away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.81,0:17:02.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But here I am, safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.44,0:17:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.73,0:17:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.07,0:17:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm doing so-so, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.94,0:17:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a novice dentist, and I'm earning money for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.74,0:17:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're a dentist now, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.70,0:17:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you did have skillful hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.91,0:17:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I had some of your social skills, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.87,0:17:21.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's true that even after the Soviets came in...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.25,0:17:23.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the reason why I'm in my current position...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.09,0:17:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is thanks to my social skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.71,0:17:30.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did enjoy myself quite a bit during the "Prague Spring."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.34,0:17:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was able to go to the West, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.47,0:17:35.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We used to talk about that a lot when we were kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.39,0:17:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About what it was like on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.98,0:17:39.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find the answer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.81,0:17:41.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.06,0:17:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.69,0:17:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was nothing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.40,0:17:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing here, nothing there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.40,0:17:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This country is making a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.40,0:17:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they aren't necessarily right on the other sider either.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.32,0:17:52.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.57,0:17:55.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said I had good social skills, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.37,0:17:58.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the truth is, there was a person\Nwho appreciated my skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.87,0:18:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I met him...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.87,0:18:04.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't really cared about\Nthe position I hold right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.75,0:18:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's such a wonderful person.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.55,0:18:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just when I came to the conclusion that there was\Nnothing in this country or on the other side...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.80,0:18:16.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he showed me a light hat I never knew existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.68,0:18:19.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's someone who brings forth something entirely new.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.56,0:18:24.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what will that person bring forth?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.56,0:18:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.94,0:18:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.53,0:18:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It could be something frightening.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.83,0:18:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I think about it now, back then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.20,0:18:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something inside of him must have started to fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.63,0:18:46.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give me back my gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.26,0:18:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, I'm giving you back your gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.01,0:18:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't, Mr. Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.01,0:18:59.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mustn't do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.52,0:19:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use trying to stop me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.10,0:19:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.94,0:19:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a family that you're living with now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.48,0:19:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's the one who killed their families.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.23,0:19:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I brought him into this country...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.40,0:19:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they were killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.32,0:19:16.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.66,0:19:18.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even my own son.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.33,0:19:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When this neighborhood was being burned down...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.12,0:19:28.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there was a man the Turks still talk about, even today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.75,0:19:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a Japanese man who tried\Nhis best to treat the injured...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.26,0:19:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and risked his life trying to put out the fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.68,0:19:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was you, wasn't it, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.18,0:19:40.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.47,0:19:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I fully understand what you're trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.52,0:19:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.19,0:19:50.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.11,0:19:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.36,0:19:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I miss this opportunity, I may\Nnever get the chance again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.82,0:19:59.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Milan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.08,0:20:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for trying to stop me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.92,0:20:11.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I was in your position...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.17,0:20:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be able to stop, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.32,0:20:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.92,0:20:51.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.38,0:20:54.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, this really is good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.34,0:20:57.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Japanese Oyakodon tastes really great!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.05,0:21:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is your leg okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.01,0:21:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want any help, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.22,0:21:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.27,0:21:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yours will be done soon, Ms. Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.77,0:21:09.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Milan sure is late.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.81,0:21:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think he'll be back soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.36,0:21:15.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's better to eat it fresh...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.90,0:21:18.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'll make his later.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.49,0:21:18.28,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In our next story...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.55,0:21:20.93,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,At 11 o'clock this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.61,0:21:19.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.45,0:21:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, I look forward to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.95,0:21:23.49,Note,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}at the Rodelheim Convention Center in Frankfurt...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.91,0:21:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}there was an incident where an\Narmed man opened fire, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.00,0:21:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the gunman was shot and killed by security\Nwho were on guard at the convention center{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.46,0:21:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There were no other victims, but...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.55,0:21:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}because a large number of important people\Nfrom various fields were attending...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.51,0:21:39.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the convention center was thrown\Ninto confusion for some time.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.55,0:21:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now, the shooter's identity and his motives\Nare still uncertain at this point.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.56,0:21:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Here's footage from the incident\Nas it happened, caught on tape.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.73,0:21:54.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone says it's really good!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.82,0:21:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope Milan comes home soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.24,0:22:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Here's footage from the incident\Nas it happened, caught on tape.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.59,0:22:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.05,0:22:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's from the Red Rose Mansion!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.88,0:22:20.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.22,0:22:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You must not hide anything from him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.84,0:22:31.01,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,471)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:44.44,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:44.44,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(201,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.44,0:22:47.40,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:23:01.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:23:01.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.68,0:23:25.94,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.94,0:23:34.36,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.36,0:23:36.82,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
